'''Facebook-剑桥分析数据丑闻'''是指英国咨询公司[[劍橋分析公司|劍橋分析公司]]在未经Facebook用户同意的情况下获取数百万Facebook用户的个人数据，這些數據主要用于[[政治廣告|政治廣告]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Cambridge Analytica whistleblower explains how the firm used Facebook data to sway elections|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-whistleblower-christopher-wylie-facebook-data-2019-10|accessdate=2020-05-07|author=Chan|first=Rosalie|work=Business Insider|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129123154/https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-whistleblower-christopher-wylie-facebook-data-2019-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Facebook的用户数据是被一款名为 "这是你的数字生活 "（This Is Your Digital Life）的应用收集<ref name=":8">{{Cite web|title=Facebook-Cambridge Analytica: A timeline of the data hijacking scandal|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/10/facebook-cambridge-analytica-a-timeline-of-the-data-hijacking-scandal.html|accessdate=2020-05-08|author=Meredith|date=2018-04-10|first=Sam|work=CNBC|language=en|archive-date=2018-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019111240/https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/10/facebook-cambridge-analytica-a-timeline-of-the-data-hijacking-scandal.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，该应用由数据科学家{{link-en|亚历山大·科根|Aleksandr Kogan}}及其公司Global Science Research于2013年开发。该应用是一款問答應用，通過提問來收集用戶的回答，并能通过Facebook的Open Graph平台收集用户的Facebook好友的个人数据。该应用獲取了多达8700万份Facebook個人用戶資料。[[劍橋分析公司|劍橋分析公司]]獲得这些数据後對此展開分析並根據分析的結果為2016年[[泰德·克鲁兹|泰德·克鲁兹]]和[[2016年唐納·川普競選美國總統|唐納·川普]]的总统竞选活动提供幫助<ref name=":9">{{Cite news|author=Confessore|first=Nicholas|date=2018-04-04|title=Cambridge Analytica and Facebook: The Scandal and the Fallout So Far|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/04/us/politics/cambridge-analytica-scandal-fallout.html|accessdate=2020-05-08|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201011222703/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/04/us/politics/cambridge-analytica-scandal-fallout.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=There's an open secret about Cambridge Analytica in the political world: It doesn't have the 'secret sauce' it claims|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-facebook-scandal-trump-cruz-operatives-2018-3|accessdate=2020-05-08|author=Smith|first=Allan|work=Business Insider|archive-date=2020-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200731112500/https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-facebook-scandal-trump-cruz-operatives-2018-3|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2018年，剑桥分析公司前员工[[克里斯托弗·怀利|克里斯托弗·怀利]]在接受《[[卫报|卫报]]》和《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》采访时向他們透露了有关Facebook数据被滥用的內幕<ref name=":10">{{Cite web|title=Facebook understood how dangerous the Trump-linked data firm Cambridge Analytica could be much earlier than it previously said. Here's everything that's happened up until now.|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-a-guide-to-the-trump-linked-data-firm-that-harvested-50-million-facebook-profiles-2018-3|accessdate=2020-05-08|author=Gilbert|first=Alexandra Ma, Ben|work=Business Insider|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126105127/https://www.businessinsider.com/cambridge-analytica-a-guide-to-the-trump-linked-data-firm-that-harvested-50-million-facebook-profiles-2018-3|dead-url=no}}</ref>。消息曝光後，Facebook为非法收據数据事件而道歉，此外Facebook的CEO[[马克·扎克伯格|马克·扎克伯格]]還不得不前往美國国会作证。2019年7月，[[聯邦貿易委員會|聯邦貿易委員會]]宣布Facebook因违反隐私规定，必須繳納50亿美元的罚款<ref name="Facebook5bn">{{Cite web|title=Facebook to be fined $5bn for Cambridge Analytica privacy violations – reports {{!}} Facebook {{!}} The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jul/12/facebook-fine-ftc-privacy-violations|accessdate=2019-07-13|work=amp.theguardian.com|archive-date=2020-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102183406/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jul/12/facebook-fine-ftc-privacy-violations|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2019年10月，Facebook同意向{{link-en|英国信息专员办公室|Information Commissioner's Office}}支付50万英镑的罚款<ref name="BBC-Fb-fine">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-50234141|title=Facebook agrees to pay Cambridge Analytica fine to UK|date=2019-10-30|language=en-US|work=BBC|accessdate=2020-10-21|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030114434/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-50234141|archivedate=2019-10-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年5月，剑桥分析公司申請破产<ref name="CAbankrupt">{{Cite web|title=Cambridge Analytica files for bankruptcy in U.S. following Facebook debacle|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL3N1SP3NP|accessdate=11 January 2021|date=18 May 2018|work=[[路透社|路透社]]|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112210141/https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL3N1SP3NP|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

这起丑闻引发了公众对社交媒体洩露個人隐私的擔憂，以至於[[Twitter|Twitter]]上有人發起#DeleteFacebook運動<ref name=":11">{{Cite news|author=Chen|first=Brian X.|date=2018-03-21|title=Want to #DeleteFacebook? You Can Try|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/21/technology/personaltech/delete-facebook.html|accessdate=2020-05-08|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130222018/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/21/technology/personaltech/delete-facebook.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[罗素兄弟|罗素兄弟]]便以此次醜聞為題材拍攝了一部电影，該電影由[[保羅·彼特尼|保羅·彼特尼]]主演<ref name="observer">{{Cite web|title=Exclusive: Paul Bettany to Co-Star in Cambridge Analytica Drama From 'Avengers' Team|url=https://observer.com/2020/03/paul-bettany-cambridge-analytica-movie-alexander-nix-facebook/|date=13 March 2020|work=[[觀察家報|觀察家報]]|accessdate=2021-01-23|archive-date=2020-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626094717/https://observer.com/2020/03/paul-bettany-cambridge-analytica-movie-alexander-nix-facebook/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

